a group that aims to provide a democratic 
alternative to chinas communist party will hold its inaugural 
congress of 120 delegates from around the world next month two 
chinese exiles say 
the congress will be held secretly in the west and will involve 
exiled student leaders and intellectuals as well as individuals 
traveling surreptitiously from china the exiles said 
the two men are wan runnan former chairman of the stone corp 
a large computer company that is one of chinas most successful 
private enterprises and yan jiaqi former member of the chinese 
academy of social sciences and a former close adviser to the 
deposed communist party leader zhao ziyang 
the pair made the announcement wednesday in manhattan 
the democratic fronts formation was announced in paris last 
month in response to the violent repression of prodemocracy forces 
in china 
the democratic front plans to serve as an umbrella organization 
for student groups chinese intellectuals and business executives 
inside china and abroad 
