sen brock adams says he will press on with 
his proposal to require new oil tankers to be built with double 
hulls despite its narrow rejection by the senate 
we were close and there is no stopping me now adams 
dwash said thursday following the 5149 vote to table and thus 
reject his amendment to a pending bill tightening oil tanker 
safety regulations and creating a special fund to clean up oil 
spills 
adams amendment would have required double hulls and double 
sides on all new tankers over 20000 deadweight tons that operate 
in us waters 
it was prompted by the exxon valdez oil spill in alaskas prince 
william sound earlier this year which adams said might not have 
grown into the nations largest oil spill ever if the vessel had 
been equipped with a double hull 
the pending bill would require that the secretary of 
transportation study for one year the use of double hulls and 
require them in new tankers unless it is found they wont enhance 
tanker safety or other structural requirements were found to be 
better 
