post that fodor entered the clinic tuesday but she did not 
identify it 
an official with new hampshires office of alcohol and drug 
abuse prevention told the associated press the state has at least 
10 private substance abuse treatment programs of the program 
officials reached by telephone thursday and today none offered any 
information about fodor being in treatment 
fodor a 39yearold denver native and winner of the 1974 
tchaikovsky violin competition in moscow was arrested july 27 on 
charges including possession of heroin and cocaine he was released 
from the edgartown mass jail monday on his own recognizance 
fodor also was charged with breaking and entering with intent to 
commit a felony after allegedly entering an unoccupied room at a 
marthas vineyard hotel police said they seized 20 grams of 
heroin some cocaine and a dagger from the violinist 
davis who lives in the washington suburb of vienna va said 
fodor called her before entering the 12step drug rehabilitation 
and counseling program he wants to do it she said 
davis who married fodor in 1978 and divorced him in 1985 said 
she could not explain how he apparently became dependent on 
narcotics 
i think everyone is confused she said however if your 
identity is tied up in what you do and things are not going the 
way you think they should youre totally frustrated and very 
vulnerable and emotional 
after great initial promise including an rca records contract 
fodors international career failed to take off and was in relative 
decline recently though he had concert bookings 
early in his career before his feet ever touched this country 
from moscow he was billed as the mick jagger of classical music 
and a playboy he came back to this whirlwind and had 90 
engagements in his first year davis said 
