<TEXT>
japans largest automobile manufacturer said friday 
it will stop using chlorofluorocarbons which are blamed for 
hurting the earths protective ozone layer 
by 1995 toyota motor corp will discontinue use of the gas 
which it uses for cleaning cooling and foaming during 
manufacturing said spokesman anthony mcmillan 
toyota used 2800 tons of cfcs during 1988 he said the toyota 
group which includes affiliated parts suppliers used 9500 tons 
in that year mcmillan said 
toyotas action follows a move by nissan motor co and honda 
motor co japans second and thirdlargest automakers to cease 
using the gas by the mid1990s 
the auto industry consumes 14 percent of all cfcs used in japan 
makers say 
in 1987 38 countries agreed in montreal to reduce production 
and use of the gases under the montreal protocol participating 
countries must have frozen their consumption of cfcs at the 1986 
level by july 1 1898 and reduce consumption to 5 percent of the 
1986 level by the end of 1999 
</TEXT>
