china said friday it would not crack down on 
intellectuals even though some participated in recent prodemocracy 
protests but it also stripped leading dissident fang lizhi of his 
post on an academic board 
the foreign ministry meanwhile refused immediate comment on 
reports by a japanese news agency that senior leader deng xiaoping 
