guilty to drugtrafficking charges 
thomas wisbey 59 was sentenced to 10 years in prison and james 
hussey 56 was given a 7year sentence for drug dealing 
both men had been convicted of participating in the great train 
robbery of aug 8 1963 when a gang of 15 men stole 7 million 
from a mail train 
you are both old enough and experienced enough to know exactly 
what you were doing and your motive was greed in each case 
regardless of the welfare of your fellow citizens judge roger 
sanders told the defendants at snaresbrook crown court in east 
london before sentencing them friday 
hussey and wisbey were each sentenced to 30 years in jail in 
1964 for their part in the train robbery hussey was released in 
december 1975 and wisbey the following year 
at a hearing in the drugs case police testified that they saw 
the two men exchanging bags containing cocaine in a park 
detective sgt martin gill told the court police seized 53 
pounds of drugs with a street value of more than 930000 
sanders ordered confiscation of about 76000 found by police at 
two addresses and with wisbeys wife irene 
