10 years for possession of cocaine with intent to supply and three 
months for possessing marijuana the sentences are to run 
concurrently 
hussey pleaded guilty of possessing 22 pounds of cocaine with 
intent to supply 
the great train robbery was planned with military precision and 
at the time was britains biggest robbery 
faking a railroad signal in the countryside northwest of london 
the gang stopped a mail train traveling from glasgow to london 
they broke into the mail van overpowered the crew and stole 
more than 120 bags full of used banknotes less than 980000 was 
recovered 
all 15 members of the gang were caught one ronald biggs 
received a 30year prison sentence but escaped from londons 
wandsworth prison on july 8 1965 he now lives in brazil immune 
from extradition because of legal technicalities 
