<TEXT>
call it the latest summer brownout 
brown suits are making a fresh appearance this year minus the 
twotone shoes and natty hats spats and cravats that your 
grandfather wore with them 
clothiers say the modern brown suit is subtler than its ancestor 
and usually has a strong tinge of blue or gray the official colors 
of the corporate office 
about 5 percent of hart schaffner amp marxs mens suits this year 
are in brown or olive shades and that share could double in 1990 
according to robert e bruno executive vice president 
last year bruno said sales were minuscule 
similar increases are being posted by greif cos whose suit 
lines include perry ellis and chaps by ralph lauren and joseph amp 
feiss co maker of cricketeer suits 
theories for the trend range from the influence of european 
fashion to nostalgia for military uniforms to attempts by the 
clothing industry to drum up sales with a new look 
chocolate brown suits are still very out despite a blip in 
sales after ronald reagan wore them 
whats in is taupe a chameleonlike brownish gray that can 
range from pale to charcoal from reddish to bluish to greenish 
brown is coming back said rick pallack a clothier to the 
stars in sherman oaks calif whose clients include talk show host 
pat sajak 
basically browns never been an important color in this 
country but taupe with off shades of different colorations that 
could be big if the retailer gets behind it said jack bier 
vice president of greif cos 
clothing manufacturers are disarmingly frank about their 
attempts to engineer interest in browns and olives to increase 
sales 
were trying to stimulate the business by obsoleting last 
years designs said bruno of hart schaffner amp marx 
jeffrey m moriber was spotted recently on manhattans 
fashionable 57th street wearing a goodlooking suit 
i would say it has a brown cast with blue influence said 
moriber creative director of a public relations agency i like 
it because it has a subtle pattern it can go either way it has 
blue tones as well as warm tones 
dressing advice books say a man in a brown suit wont be taken 
seriously but taupe may be another matter its peculiar beauty is 
that no one can quite describe it 
websters third new international dictionary says taupe comes 
from the latin talpa for mole and calls it a brownish gray that 
is paler and slightly yellower than chocolate duller and slightly 
redder than mouse gray and duller and slightly redder than 
castor 
we started seeing it about five years ago said rick white 
a salesman at the tailored man in san francisco it can have a 
green cast or an olive cast or a purple cast its hard to 
define 
for fall and winter taupe will carry on in its darker tones as 
a thread or accent color in a pinstripe windowpane or subtle plaid 
