the dollar rose nearly 2 percent friday against 
major foreign currencies its biggest gain in months after a 
government report upset expectations of an economic slowdown 
the dollars rally was the mirror image of a debacle in the bond 
market the selling binge in bonds drove interest yields higher and 
made the dollardenominated securities more attractive to global 
investors 
gold prices fell in us trading after finishing higher overseas 
the dollar remained well below the peaks reached in june in 
spite of its oneday surge which amounted to 19 percent against 
the west german mark british pound and japanese yen and an even 2 
percent vs the swiss franc 
