nonfarm payrolls rose by 169000 in july 
although the figure was consistent with economists predictions 
many traders had been betting that payroll growth would be much 
smaller also the department revised upward the figure for june 
job growth 
the job statistics renewed fears of inflation which hurts the 
value of interestpaying securities as a result bond prices fell 
and their yields shot up 
