los angeles investor alfred checchi signed 
the acquisition papers friday to complete his groups 365 billion 
buyout of nwa inc the parent of northwest airlines 
the 41yearold former marriott corp treasurer said all 
publicly held shares of nwa common stock have been purchased for 
121 each officially ending the takeover battle initiated by 
checchi in late march 
checchi has said he will spend some of his time at nwas eagan 
minn headquarters but will not take a management position steven 
rothmeier will stay on as the companys chief executive officer and 
chairman while checchi will become a board member a spokesman for 
the airline said 
as a result of the takeover moodys investors service announced 
friday it has lowered the senior debt ratings of nwa to singleb1 
from baa2 and of northwest to ba2 from singlea3 about 400 
million of longterm debt is affected the credit rating agency 
said 
checchis group described early on by rothmeier as a friendly 
suitor beat out at least three other bidders rival airline pan am 
corp the 20000member machinists union local at northwest and 
los angeles oil billionaire marvin davis who started the public 
bidding with an offer of 27 billion or 90 a share on march 28 
checchi who once worked for the bass brothers of fort worth 
texas financed the takeover with 700 million cash and another 
335 billion in financing from commercial banks led by bankers 
trust co equity partners include klm royal dutch airlines and 
elders finance group of australia neither of which are allowed a 
controlling interest under laws that limit foreign investment in 
us airlines 
the deal did not require government approval but checchis 
group will need an operating permit from the us transportation 
department which is conducting a financial fitness review of the 
new owners checchi has said it is laughable to think that the 
permit would be withheld 
he acquires an airline in the midst of tense contract talks with 
its 5000 pilots the pilots have been without a contract for about 
2 years and have asked the national mediation board to declare an 
impasse in the negotiations if the request is granted the pilots 
would be free to strike legally after a 30day coolingoff 
period 
checchi is depending on a steady cash flow to service the large 
takeover debt and a pilots strike could idle the carrier 
checchi also inherits an airline that earned the nickname 
northworst after a prolonged performance slump that followed 
the 1986 purchase of republic airlines the carrier has vastly 
improved its service however and earnings are on the rise 
after posting record earnings in 1988 of 135 million or 463 
a share nwa is positioned to surpass that mark it earned 833 
million or 282 a share in the first six months of this year 
of the 212 billion revenue passenger miles logged by 
northwests 314 planes in the first six months of the year 126 
billion miles were domestic and 73 billion were flown on routes to 
the pacific rim where northwest has the largest presence of any 
us carrier a revenue passenger mile represents one paying 
passenger flown one mile 
checchi has vowed to keep the companys headquarters in eagan a 
st paul suburb minutes from the minneapolisst paul international 
airport and he has said the jobs of the carriers 37590 employees 
are secure 
