international said he doesnt buy the argument that the 
employment report was that strong 
he said the market is more concerned about absorbing the 295 
billion in new securities that the treasury plans to auction next 
week 
in addition he said the market is wary about the new supply of 
issues that may be headed its way as a result of a compromise 
between the white house and congress on a rescue package for the 
nations savings and loans 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds prices of shortterm 
governments fell point to a full point intermediate maturities 
lost 1 point to 1 points and longterm issues fell as much as 2 
points according to telerate inc the financial information 
service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
