money in the second quarter than it did in the same period last 
year 
pan am reported a net loss of 77 million for the quarter 
compared with a loss of 5 million in the same quarter last year 
the nations eighthlargest airline company said revenue of its 
main subsidiary pan american world airways continued to suffer 
from lower international traffic in the wake of the pan am crash 
over scotland last december 
the latest loss occurred despite aggressive pricing actions 
and some benefit from the strike affecting rival eastern airlines 
pan am said 
the results for the latest quarter include a gain of 921 
million on the sale of the companys pan am world services unit and 
expenses of 282 million stemming from its unsuccessful takeover 
bid for nwa inc the parent of rival northwest airlines 
total revenue for the second quarter declined 17 percent to 
9094 million from 9254 million a year earlier 
combined revenue from the pan am shuttle and pan am express a 
commuter airline subsidiary jumped 478 percent to 832 million 
from 563 million partly offsetting the decline at pan american 
world airways 
